{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":1773482700893,"sessionID":"ses_3143289ffffebE5N0evuhJd5Hx","part":{"id":"prt_cebce6e08001ZbCIpN3u0uWAx0","sessionID":"ses_3143289ffffebE5N0evuhJd5Hx","messageID":"msg_cebce2550001NO5YXygOi1stMZ","type":"tool","callID":"toolu_vrtx_01Pz6pSeNi5MoiQcnBBBaZFe","tool":"read","state":{"status":"completed","input":{"filePath":"/home/fulgidus/Documents/wombo-combo-worktrees/wave-reconnect/src/lib/monitor.ts","offset":363,"limit":230},"output":"<path>/home/fulgidus/Documents/wombo-combo-worktrees/wave-reconnect/src/lib/monitor.ts</path>\n<type>file</type>\n<content>363: export class ProcessMonitor {\n364:   private processes: Map<string, MonitoredProcess> = new Map();\n365:   private callbacks: MonitorCallbacks;\n366:   private logDir: string;\n367:   /** Per-agent activity log for TUI preview pane */\n368:   public activityLogs: Map<string, ActivityEntry[]> = new Map();\n369:   /** Token usage collector — parses and accumulates usage from step_finish events */\n370:   public tokenCollector: TokenCollector;\n371: \n372:   constructor(projectRoot: string, callbacks: MonitorCallbacks = {}) {\n373:     this.callbacks = callbacks;\n374:     this.logDir = resolve(projectRoot, LOG_DIR_NAME);\n375:     if (!existsSync(this.logDir)) {\n376:       mkdirSync(this.logDir, { recursive: true });\n377:     }\n378:     this.tokenCollector = new TokenCollector((record) => {\n379:       this.callbacks.onUsage?.(record.task_id, record);\n380:     });\n381:   }\n382: \n383:   private pushActivity(featureId: string, text: string): void {\n384:     if (!this.activityLogs.has(featureId)) {\n385:       this.activityLogs.set(featureId, []);\n386:     }\n387:     const log = this.activityLogs.get(featureId)!;\n388:     for (const line of text.split(\"\\n\")) {\n389:       log.push({ timestamp: new Date().toISOString().slice(11, 19), text: line });\n390:     }\n391:     if (log.length > MAX_ACTIVITY_LINES) {\n392:       log.splice(0, log.length - MAX_ACTIVITY_LINES);\n393:     }\n394:   }\n395: \n396:   private writeLog(featureId: string, data: string): void {\n397:     try {\n398:       const logFile = resolve(this.logDir, `${featureId}.log`);\n399:       appendFileSync(logFile, data);\n400:     } catch {\n401:       // Non-critical\n402:     }\n403:   }\n404: \n405:   getActivityLog(featureId: string): ActivityEntry[] {\n406:     return this.activityLogs.get(featureId) ?? [];\n407:   }\n408: \n409:   addProcess(featureId: string, child: ChildProcess): void {\n410:     const monitored: MonitoredProcess = {\n411:       featureId,\n412:       process: child,\n413:       stdout: \"\",\n414:       stderr: \"\",\n415:       sessionId: null,\n416:       done: false,\n417:       lineBuffer: \"\",\n418:       sawFinalStop: false,\n419:     };\n420: \n421:     this.pushActivity(featureId, \"-- agent process started\");\n422:     this.writeLog(featureId, `[wombo] Process started at ${new Date().toISOString()}\\n`);\n423: \n424:     child.stdout?.on(\"data\", (data: Buffer) => {\n425:       const chunk = data.toString();\n426:       monitored.stdout += chunk;\n427:       this.callbacks.onOutput?.(featureId, chunk);\n428:       this.writeLog(featureId, chunk);\n429: \n430:       monitored.lineBuffer += chunk;\n431:       const lines = monitored.lineBuffer.split(\"\\n\");\n432:       monitored.lineBuffer = lines.pop() ?? \"\";\n433: \n434:       for (const line of lines) {\n435:         const trimmed = line.trim();\n436:         if (!trimmed) continue;\n437:         try {\n438:           const event = JSON.parse(trimmed) as OpenCodeEvent;\n439: \n440:           if (!monitored.sessionId && event.sessionID) {\n441:             monitored.sessionId = event.sessionID;\n442:             this.callbacks.onSessionId?.(featureId, event.sessionID);\n443:             this.pushActivity(featureId, `-- session: ${event.sessionID}`);\n444:           }\n445: \n446:           const activity = extractActivity(event);\n447:           if (activity) {\n448:             this.callbacks.onActivity?.(featureId, activity);\n449:           }\n450: \n451:           const logLine = formatEventForLog(event);\n452:           if (logLine) {\n453:             this.pushActivity(featureId, logLine);\n454:           }\n455: \n456:           // Extract token usage from step_finish events\n457:           this.tokenCollector.ingestEvent(featureId, event);\n458: \n459:           if (\n460:             event.type === \"step_finish\" &&\n461:             event.part?.reason === \"stop\"\n462:           ) {\n463:             monitored.sawFinalStop = true;\n464:           }\n465:         } catch {\n466:           if (trimmed.length > 0 && trimmed.length < 500) {\n467:             this.pushActivity(featureId, `[raw] ${trimmed.slice(0, 120)}`);\n468:           }\n469:         }\n470:       }\n471:     });\n472: \n473:     child.stderr?.on(\"data\", (data: Buffer) => {\n474:       const chunk = data.toString();\n475:       monitored.stderr += chunk;\n476:       this.writeLog(featureId, `[stderr] ${chunk}`);\n477:       const lines = chunk.split(\"\\n\").filter((l) => l.trim());\n478:       for (const line of lines) {\n479:         this.pushActivity(featureId, `[stderr] ${line.trim().slice(0, 120)}`);\n480:       }\n481:     });\n482: \n483:     child.on(\"exit\", (code) => {\n484:       monitored.done = true;\n485:       this.pushActivity(featureId, `-- process exited (code ${code})`);\n486:       this.writeLog(featureId, `\\n[wombo] Process exited with code ${code} at ${new Date().toISOString()}\\n`);\n487: \n488:       if (code === 0 || monitored.sawFinalStop) {\n489:         this.callbacks.onComplete?.(featureId);\n490:       } else {\n491:         const error =\n492:           monitored.stderr.slice(-2000) ||\n493:           `Process exited with code ${code}`;\n494:         this.callbacks.onError?.(featureId, error);\n495:       }\n496:     });\n497: \n498:     child.on(\"error\", (err) => {\n499:       monitored.done = true;\n500:       this.pushActivity(featureId, `!! process error: ${err.message}`);\n501:       this.writeLog(featureId, `\\n[wombo] Process error: ${err.message}\\n`);\n502:       this.callbacks.onError?.(featureId, err.message);\n503:     });\n504: \n505:     this.processes.set(featureId, monitored);\n506:   }\n507: \n508:   getSessionId(featureId: string): string | null {\n509:     return this.processes.get(featureId)?.sessionId ?? null;\n510:   }\n511: \n512:   getOutput(featureId: string): string {\n513:     return this.processes.get(featureId)?.stdout ?? \"\";\n514:   }\n515: \n516:   isRunning(featureId: string): boolean {\n517:     const m = this.processes.get(featureId);\n518:     if (!m) return false;\n519:     if (m.done) return false;\n520:     return isProcessRunning(m.process.pid!);\n521:   }\n522: \n523:   allDone(): boolean {\n524:     for (const m of this.processes.values()) {\n525:       if (!m.done) return false;\n526:     }\n527:     return true;\n528:   }\n529: \n530:   activeCount(): number {\n531:     let count = 0;\n532:     for (const m of this.processes.values()) {\n533:       if (!m.done) count++;\n534:     }\n535:     return count;\n536:   }\n537: \n538:   /**\n539:    * Remove a process from monitoring and kill it if still running.\n540:    *\n541:    * Sends SIGTERM (not SIGKILL) to allow the agent to handle shutdown\n542:    * gracefully (e.g., save partial work, close files). The process map\n543:    * entry is deleted immediately — any subsequent events from the dying\n544:    * process are ignored.\n545:    */\n546:   remove(featureId: string): void {\n547:     const m = this.processes.get(featureId);\n548:     if (m && !m.done) {\n549:       try {\n550:         m.process.kill(\"SIGTERM\");\n551:       } catch {}\n552:     }\n553:     this.processes.delete(featureId);\n554:   }\n555: \n556:   /**\n557:    * Kill all monitored processes. Called during graceful shutdown\n558:    * (SIGINT, TUI quit) to ensure no orphaned agent processes remain.\n559:    *\n560:    * This is the primary teardown path. After killAll(), the parent\n561:    * process saves wave state and exits. Agents can be re-launched\n562:    * later via `woco resume`.\n563:    */\n564:   killAll(): void {\n565:     for (const id of this.processes.keys()) {\n566:       this.remove(id);\n567:     }\n568:   }\n569: \n570:   waitAll(pollIntervalMs: number = 1000): Promise<void> {\n571:     return new Promise((resolve) => {\n572:       const check = () => {\n573:         if (this.allDone()) {\n574:           resolve();\n575:         } else {\n576:           setTimeout(check, pollIntervalMs);\n577:         }\n578:       };\n579:       check();\n580:     });\n581:   }\n582: }\n583: \n584: // ---------------------------------------------------------------------------\n585: // Re-exports from token-collector for convenience\n586: // ---------------------------------------------------------------------------\n587: \n588: export { TokenCollector, type UsageRecord } from \"./token-collector.js\";\n589: export type { UsageSummary, UsageCallback } from \"./token-collector.js\";\n\n(End of file - total 589 lines)\n</content>","title":"src/lib/monitor.ts","metadata":{"preview":"export class ProcessMonitor {\n  private processes: Map<string, MonitoredProcess> = new Map();\n  private callbacks: MonitorCallbacks;\n  private logDir: string;\n  /** Per-agent activity log for TUI preview pane */\n  public activityLogs: Map<string, ActivityEntry[]> = new Map();\n  /** Token usage collector — parses and accumulates usage from step_finish events */\n  public tokenCollector: TokenCollector;\n\n  constructor(projectRoot: string, callbacks: MonitorCallbacks = {}) {\n    this.callbacks = callbacks;\n    this.logDir = resolve(projectRoot, LOG_DIR_NAME);\n    if (!existsSync(this.logDir)) {\n      mkdirSync(this.logDir, { recursive: true });\n    }\n    this.tokenCollector = new TokenCollector((record) => {\n      this.callbacks.onUsage?.(record.task_id, record);\n    });\n  }\n","truncated":false,"loaded":[]},"time":{"start":1773482700889,"end":1773482700892}}}}
{"type":"text","timestamp":1773482700901,"sessionID":"ses_3143289ffffebE5N0evuhJd5Hx","part":{"id":"prt_cebce2dff002MJLZAoE6wubX7G","sessionID":"ses_3143289ffffebE5N0evuhJd5Hx","messageID":"msg_cebce2550001NO5YXygOi1stMZ","type":"text","text":"Good. The log files are at `.wombo-combo/logs/<featureId>.log`. Now I understand the flow:\n\nWhen a headless agent runs, its stdout is piped to the parent process (via `child.stdout`). The ProcessMonitor:\n1. Attaches stdout/stderr data listeners to parse JSON events in real-time\n2. Writes raw output to `.wombo-combo/logs/<featureId>.log` via `appendFileSync`\n\nWhen reconnecting after a quit:\n- The ChildProcess handles are gone (they were tied to the old parent process)\n- But the agent is still running (if PID is alive) and is still writing to stdout — which nobody is reading anymore\n- The log file has the historical output but isn't being tailed\n\nFor the reconnection approach, since the agents were spawned with `detached: false` and `stdio: [\"pipe\", \"pipe\", \"pipe\"]`, when the parent dies the pipes break. The agents likely die too. But if they're still alive (e.g., the parent exited gracefully via `process.exit(0)` after `killAll()`), there's no way to reattach to their stdout.\n\nHowever, looking more carefully at the code, I see the actual flow:\n\n1. When user presses Q, `onQuit` is called\n2. `onQuit` calls `monitor.killAll()` which sends SIGTERM to all agents\n3. Then `process.exit(0)` is called\n\nSo agents get killed on quit! The PIDs should be dead when resuming. But the task description says \"Detect running agent processes from state file PIDs\" — this handles the case where:\n1. The parent was SIGKILL'd (agents die too since `detached: false`)\n2. Interactive mode agents (tmux/dmux sessions) that survive parent death\n3. Some edge case where processes outlive the parent\n\nLet me re-read the existing resume logic more carefully — specifically the part about PID-alive agents:\n\nIn resume.ts, line 166-167:\n```typescript\nif (agent.pid && isProcessRunning(agent.pid)) {\n  if (fmt === \"text\") console.log(`  ${agent.feature_id}: still running (PID ${agent.pid}), leaving alone`);\n```\n\nThis is the key issue — when an agent is \"still running\", it's left alone with no monitoring. The monitoring loop later checks for dead PIDs but never reconnects to the live ones for log tailing.\n\nThe solution:\n1. Add a `reconnectProcess()` method to `ProcessMonitor` that sets up PID-based polling (since we can't reattach to stdout) and tails the log file for activity updates\n2. Have resume.ts use this method for PID-alive agents\n3. The reconnected process will be monitored via PID polling for liveness, and the log file will be tailed for activity\n\nLet me implement this:","time":{"start":1773482700901,"end":1773482700901}}}
