{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":1773482726946,"sessionID":"ses_3143289ffffebE5N0evuhJd5Hx","part":{"id":"prt_cebced004001wrWHuctE5cqMFU","sessionID":"ses_3143289ffffebE5N0evuhJd5Hx","messageID":"msg_cebce70e10014hmeZKhNH2O8nv","type":"tool","callID":"toolu_vrtx_01TVVRG9djkhnwAp2qBaQDcA","tool":"grep","state":{"status":"completed","input":{"pattern":"monitor\\.isRunning|isRunning\\(","include":"*.ts","path":"/home/fulgidus/Documents/wombo-combo-worktrees/wave-reconnect/src"},"output":"Found 4 matches\n/home/fulgidus/Documents/wombo-combo-worktrees/wave-reconnect/src/lib/monitor.ts:\n  Line 516:   isRunning(featureId: string): boolean {\n\n/home/fulgidus/Documents/wombo-combo-worktrees/wave-reconnect/src/commands/resume.ts:\n  Line 650:           !monitor.isRunning(agent.feature_id)\n\n/home/fulgidus/Documents/wombo-combo-worktrees/wave-reconnect/src/commands/launch.ts:\n  Line 1238:         !monitor.isRunning(agent.feature_id)\n  Line 1288:         !monitor.isRunning(agent.feature_id)","title":"monitor\\.isRunning|isRunning\\(","metadata":{"matches":4,"truncated":false},"time":{"start":1773482726943,"end":1773482726946}}}}
{"type":"text","timestamp":1773482726957,"sessionID":"ses_3143289ffffebE5N0evuhJd5Hx","part":{"id":"prt_cebce793c001Tv5OKT3pvC9PEI","sessionID":"ses_3143289ffffebE5N0evuhJd5Hx","messageID":"msg_cebce70e10014hmeZKhNH2O8nv","type":"text","text":"Now I need to understand the key architectural insight: when agents are spawned with `detached: false` and `stdio: pipe`, when the parent exits, the pipes break and agents get SIGTERM (from `killAll()`). So when we \"resume\", agents should generally be dead.\n\nBut there are important edge cases:\n1. Interactive mode agents (tmux/dmux) survive parent death\n2. If the parent crashed with SIGKILL, agents with `detached: false` die too (no opportunity for killAll)\n3. The state file might have stale PIDs\n\nThe key insight for the task: when the user quits the TUI (Q key), `killAll()` sends SIGTERM but `process.exit(0)` is called immediately after. Agents may not have fully exited yet. More importantly, **there's actually no way to reattach to stdout of an already-running process** in Node/Bun.\n\nSo the reconnection strategy should be:\n1. **Detect still-running processes via `kill(pid, 0)`** — if alive, tail the log file\n2. **If dead, update state** — mark as completed (if has changes) or failed (if no changes)\n3. **Tail the log file** for activity — since the log file was being written to by the ProcessMonitor, when the parent died, the agent's stdout pipe broke. But for interactive agents (mux mode), they're still running independently.\n\nWait, I need to reconsider. The log file is written by the **parent** process (ProcessMonitor.writeLog), not by the agent. When the parent dies, log writing stops. So for truly still-running agents, there's no log file being updated.\n\nHowever, there IS a scenario where this matters: **interactive (mux) agents**. These run in tmux/dmux sessions and are independent. They don't have piped stdout — the parent can't tail them. The TUI currently just shows \"leaving alone.\"\n\nLet me re-examine the actual intent. Looking at the task description again:\n\n> When re-entering the wave monitor after previously quitting while agents were running:\n> 1) Detect running agent processes from state file PIDs\n> 2) Re-attach stdout/stderr streams for log tailing\n> 3) Resume the ProcessMonitor polling loop\n> 4) If a process died while monitor was closed, detect via kill(pid, 0) and update state accordingly\n\nFor headless agents, we can't re-attach stdout (the pipe is broken when parent exits). But we CAN:\n1. Register the PID in the monitor as a \"reconnected process\" (no ChildProcess handle, just PID-based polling)\n2. Tail the existing log file for historical activity  \n3. Poll PID for liveness and detect when it dies\n4. The polling loop in resume.ts already handles dead PIDs — but it only works if the agent is in the monitor's process map\n\nLet me implement this properly now. The approach:\n\n1. Add `reconnectProcess(featureId, pid, sessionId)` to ProcessMonitor — creates a \"virtual\" MonitoredProcess with no ChildProcess handle, just PID + done=false\n2. Load historical activity from the log file \n3. The existing `isRunning()` method needs updating since it uses `m.process.pid!` which would be null for reconnected processes\n4. The `remove()` method needs to handle processes without a ChildProcess handle\n5. The existing polling loop in resume.ts/launch.ts will detect when the PID dies\n\nLet me also look at how `isRunning` is used more carefully:","time":{"start":1773482726956,"end":1773482726956}}}
{"type":"step_finish","timestamp":1773482727071,"sessionID":"ses_3143289ffffebE5N0evuhJd5Hx","part":{"id":"prt_cebced62d001mFBN3rGgJxI4Rh","sessionID":"ses_3143289ffffebE5N0evuhJd5Hx","messageID":"msg_cebce70e10014hmeZKhNH2O8nv","type":"step-finish","reason":"tool-calls","snapshot":"ad79631b6608fcbb290601e7179a7823bccd9901","cost":0,"tokens":{"total":99599,"input":3524,"output":945,"reasoning":0,"cache":{"read":95130,"write":0}}}}
{"type":"step_start","timestamp":1773482729998,"sessionID":"ses_3143289ffffebE5N0evuhJd5Hx","part":{"id":"prt_cebcee20d0016dnj02X6CPBG03","sessionID":"ses_3143289ffffebE5N0evuhJd5Hx","messageID":"msg_cebced6ab001zmXNIlnebzFf1b","type":"step-start","snapshot":"ad79631b6608fcbb290601e7179a7823bccd9901"}}
{"type":"text","timestamp":1773482761402,"sessionID":"ses_3143289ffffebE5N0evuhJd5Hx","part":{"id":"prt_cebcee20e001pSbsHKFbQhDvfA","sessionID":"ses_3143289ffffebE5N0evuhJd5Hx","messageID":"msg_cebced6ab001zmXNIlnebzFf1b","type":"text","text":"## Goal\n\nImplement a \"reconnect to running agents\" feature for the wombo-combo orchestration system. When a user quits the wave monitor TUI while agents are still running, then re-enters (via `woco resume` or `woco`), the system should:\n1. Detect running agent processes from state file PIDs using `kill(pid, 0)`\n2. Re-attach stdout/stderr streams for log tailing (or use log file tailing as fallback)\n3. Resume the ProcessMonitor polling loop\n4. If a process died while the monitor was closed, detect and update state accordingly\n\n**Feature ID:** `wave-reconnect` | **Branch:** `feature/wave-reconnect` | **Base:** `main`\n\n## Instructions\n\n- Use conventional commits scoped to `wave-reconnect`\n- Commit after each logical unit of work (per subtask)\n- Do NOT squash commits or push to remote\n- Do NOT modify `tasks` directory\n- Run `bun run build` to verify everything works before considering done\n- Use Bun APIs where available, ESM only, TypeScript strict mode\n- Use `bun dev` (not global `wombo` binary) for testing\n- Use `portless run` when starting any localhost server\n\n## Discoveries\n\n### Architecture Understanding\n\n1. **Headless agents** are spawned with `detached: false` and `stdio: [\"pipe\", \"pipe\", \"pipe\"]`. When the parent exits, pipes break and agents get SIGTERM (from `killAll()` in the quit handler). So headless agents are generally dead when resuming.\n\n2. **Interactive agents** (tmux/dmux) run independently and survive parent death. These are the primary case where PIDs may still be alive on resume.\n\n3. **Log files** at `.wombo-combo/logs/<featureId>.log` are written by the **parent process** (ProcessMonitor.writeLog), not by the agent directly. When the parent dies, log writing stops.\n\n4. **Current resume behavior** (the bug): When `cmdResume` finds an agent with a still-alive PID, it just prints \"leaving alone\" and does NOT add it to the ProcessMonitor. This means:\n   - No TUI activity display for that agent\n   - The polling loop checks `!monitor.isRunning(agent.feature_id)` which returns `false` (not in monitor), combined with `!isProcessRunning(agent.pid)` — so it only acts when the PID dies\n   - But there's no monitoring, log tailing, or activity tracking for the live agent\n\n5. **ProcessMonitor.isRunning()** uses `m.process.pid!` which requires a ChildProcess handle — this needs updating for reconnected processes that only have a PID.\n\n6. **ProcessMonitor.remove()** calls `m.process.kill(\"SIGTERM\")` — needs to handle reconnected processes that have no ChildProcess handle (should use `process.kill(pid, 'SIGTERM')` instead).\n\n7. The `MonitoredProcess` interface has `process: ChildProcess` which will need to be optional for reconnected processes.\n\n### Implementation Plan\n\nThe approach should be:\n\n1. **In `monitor.ts`**: Add `reconnectProcess(featureId, pid, sessionId?)` method that:\n   - Creates a \"virtual\" `MonitoredProcess` with no ChildProcess handle, just PID + `done=false`\n   - Loads historical activity from the existing log file (last N lines)\n   - The existing polling loop in resume.ts will handle PID death detection\n   - Update `isRunning()` to work with PID-only entries (no `m.process.pid!`)\n   - Update `remove()` to send SIGTERM via `process.kill(pid, signal)` for reconnected processes\n   - Make `process` field on `MonitoredProcess` nullable\n\n2. **In `resume.ts`**: When an agent's PID is alive, call `monitor.reconnectProcess()` instead of just logging \"leaving alone\". This registers the agent in the monitor so the TUI shows it and the polling loop can detect death.\n\n3. **In `commands/tui.ts`**: The existing flow already calls `cmdResume` which will now properly reconnect — may need minor adjustments.\n\n## Accomplished\n\n- ✅ Read and analyzed all key files in detail\n- ✅ Created initial TODO plan\n- ✅ Identified the exact bug and designed the solution\n- ✅ Understood the full architecture (headless vs interactive, process lifecycle, log files, TUI)\n- ❌ No code has been written yet — implementation has not started\n\n## Relevant files / directories\n\n### Key files to modify:\n- `/home/fulgidus/Documents/wombo-combo-worktrees/wave-reconnect/src/lib/monitor.ts` — Add `reconnectProcess()` method, update `MonitoredProcess` interface, update `isRunning()`, `remove()`, `killAll()`\n- `/home/fulgidus/Documents/wombo-combo-worktrees/wave-reconnect/src/commands/resume.ts` — Update headless resume path (line ~166) to call `monitor.reconnectProcess()` for PID-alive agents\n- `/home/fulgidus/Documents/wombo-combo-worktrees/wave-reconnect/src/commands/tui.ts` — May need minor adjustments for reconnection flow\n\n### Files read for context (no changes needed):\n- `/home/fulgidus/Documents/wombo-combo-worktrees/wave-reconnect/src/lib/state.ts` — WaveState, AgentState types, loadState/saveState\n- `/home/fulgidus/Documents/wombo-combo-worktrees/wave-reconnect/src/lib/launcher.ts` — launchHeadless, isProcessRunning, spawn config (`detached: false`)\n- `/home/fulgidus/Documents/wombo-combo-worktrees/wave-reconnect/src/lib/tui.ts` — WomboTUI class, how it uses ProcessMonitor\n- `/home/fulgidus/Documents/wombo-combo-worktrees/wave-reconnect/src/commands/launch.ts` — launchWaveHeadless, polling loop, shared helpers\n- `/home/fulgidus/Documents/wombo-combo-worktrees/wave-reconnect/src/lib/token-collector.ts` — TokenCollector class\n- `/home/fulgidus/Documents/wombo-combo-worktrees/wave-reconnect/src/config.ts` — WomboConfig type\n- `/home/fulgidus/Documents/wombo-combo-worktrees/wave-reconnect/AGENTS.md` — Project conventions\n- `/home/fulgidus/Documents/wombo-combo-worktrees/wave-reconnect/package.json` — Build scripts, dependencies","time":{"start":1773482761401,"end":1773482761401}}}
