{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":1773482890571,"sessionID":"ses_3143289ffffebE5N0evuhJd5Hx","part":{"id":"prt_cebd1513b001ZrcFEzeuW2d1Bs","sessionID":"ses_3143289ffffebE5N0evuhJd5Hx","messageID":"msg_cebd1393b0016TK5lpN4EOvkWA","type":"tool","callID":"toolu_vrtx_019aQcPG892xZ4RcHZYAgtfm","tool":"read","state":{"status":"completed","input":{"filePath":"/home/fulgidus/Documents/wombo-combo-worktrees/wave-reconnect/src/commands/resume.ts","limit":40,"offset":155},"output":"<path>/home/fulgidus/Documents/wombo-combo-worktrees/wave-reconnect/src/commands/resume.ts</path>\n<type>file</type>\n<content>155:   // Triage agents by current state\n156:   let toRelaunch: AgentState[] = [];\n157:   let toVerify: AgentState[] = [];\n158: \n159:   for (const agent of state.agents) {\n160:     switch (agent.status) {\n161:       case \"running\":\n162:       case \"installing\":\n163:       case \"retry\":\n164:       case \"resolving_conflict\":\n165:         // Was in-flight when we stopped — check if PID is still alive\n166:         if (agent.pid && isProcessRunning(agent.pid)) {\n167:           if (fmt === \"text\") console.log(`  ${agent.feature_id}: still running (PID ${agent.pid}), leaving alone`);\n168:         } else {\n169:           // Process is dead — check if worktree exists with meaningful changes.\n170:           // Use worktreeExists (not worktreeReady) because node_modules may be\n171:           // missing — the worktree still has code that should be verified.\n172:           if (worktreeExists(agent.worktree) && branchHasChanges(projectRoot, agent.branch, state.base_branch)) {\n173:             // Worktree exists AND branch has commits — try build verification\n174:             if (fmt === \"text\") console.log(`  ${agent.feature_id}: process dead, worktree has changes — will verify build`);\n175:             toVerify.push(agent);\n176:           } else {\n177:             // No worktree, or worktree exists but branch has no commits (agent did nothing)\n178:             const reason = worktreeExists(agent.worktree)\n179:               ? \"worktree exists but no code changes\"\n180:               : \"no worktree\";\n181:             if (fmt === \"text\") console.log(`  ${agent.feature_id}: process dead, ${reason} — will re-launch`);\n182:             updateAgent(state, agent.feature_id, {\n183:               status: \"queued\",\n184:               pid: null,\n185:               activity: null,\n186:               session_id: null,\n187:             });\n188:             toRelaunch.push(agent);\n189:           }\n190:         }\n191:         break;\n192: \n193:       case \"queued\":\n194:         if (fmt === \"text\") console.log(`  ${agent.feature_id}: queued — will launch`);\n\n(Showing lines 155-194 of 769. Use offset=195 to continue.)\n</content>","title":"src/commands/resume.ts","metadata":{"preview":"  // Triage agents by current state\n  let toRelaunch: AgentState[] = [];\n  let toVerify: AgentState[] = [];\n\n  for (const agent of state.agents) {\n    switch (agent.status) {\n      case \"running\":\n      case \"installing\":\n      case \"retry\":\n      case \"resolving_conflict\":\n        // Was in-flight when we stopped — check if PID is still alive\n        if (agent.pid && isProcessRunning(agent.pid)) {\n          if (fmt === \"text\") console.log(`  ${agent.feature_id}: still running (PID ${agent.pid}), leaving alone`);\n        } else {\n          // Process is dead — check if worktree exists with meaningful changes.\n          // Use worktreeExists (not worktreeReady) because node_modules may be\n          // missing — the worktree still has code that should be verified.\n          if (worktreeExists(agent.worktree) && branchHasChanges(projectRoot, agent.branch, state.base_branch)) {\n            // Worktree exists AND branch has commits — try build verification\n            if (fmt === \"text\") console.log(`  ${agent.feature_id}: process dead, worktree has changes — will verify build`);","truncated":true,"loaded":[]},"time":{"start":1773482890567,"end":1773482890570}}}}
{"type":"text","timestamp":1773482890574,"sessionID":"ses_3143289ffffebE5N0evuhJd5Hx","part":{"id":"prt_cebd14142002dR47BaZ0e5qrnP","sessionID":"ses_3143289ffffebE5N0evuhJd5Hx","messageID":"msg_cebd1393b0016TK5lpN4EOvkWA","type":"text","text":"### Step 5: Update resume.ts — headless resume path\n\nThe key area is in the headless resume section (around line 497+). Currently, agents with PIDs still alive are triaged in the initial `for` loop (line 159-192) with \"leaving alone\" — and these agents are NOT included in `toRelaunch`, so they never get added to the monitor.\n\nI need to:\n1. Track which agents have live PIDs during triage\n2. After creating the ProcessMonitor, call `monitor.reconnectProcess()` for each live agent\n\nLet me look at the triage section more carefully:","time":{"start":1773482890574,"end":1773482890574}}}
