{"type":"text","timestamp":1773482919433,"sessionID":"ses_3143289ffffebE5N0evuhJd5Hx","part":{"id":"prt_cebd1afa6002Vfg3bHJEpkPbjm","sessionID":"ses_3143289ffffebE5N0evuhJd5Hx","messageID":"msg_cebd1a89d001aME5kLl1RgHbiC","type":"text","text":"Now I also need to handle the `killAll()` behavior for reconnected processes in the SIGINT handler. The `killAll()` call already works correctly because the updated `remove()` method handles both cases (ChildProcess and PID-only). However, for reconnected processes we may NOT want to kill them on quit — they're independent mux agents that should survive. Let me think about this...\n\nActually, looking at the architecture: the **headless resume** path is for headless agents. But if we look at the triage, `stillAlive` agents in headless mode are typically interactive (mux) agents that survived the parent's death. In the headless resume path, killing them on quit would be wrong.\n\nLet me add a parameter to `remove()` to optionally skip killing, and update `killAll()` to skip killing reconnected processes:","time":{"start":1773482919433,"end":1773482919433}}}
