nt.worktree)) {\n            await createWorktree(projectRoot, agent.feature_id, state.base_branch, config);\n            await installDeps(agent.worktree, agent.feature_id, config);\n          }","truncated":true,"loaded":[]},"time":{"start":1773482954409,"end":1773482954412}}}}
{"type":"text","timestamp":1773482954425,"sessionID":"ses_3143289ffffebE5N0evuhJd5Hx","part":{"id":"prt_cebd24074001dsm1Qu7awAE23F","sessionID":"ses_3143289ffffebE5N0evuhJd5Hx","messageID":"msg_cebd238a0001PH12JAkqgEhVSC","type":"text","text":"Build passes. Let me also check the interactive resume path in resume.ts — the `stillAlive` agents are only reconnected in the headless path. In the interactive path (line 428+), agents are re-launched into new mux sessions, so the still-alive ones would remain unhandled. Let me look:","time":{"start":1773482954424,"end":1773482954424}}}
