{"type":"text","timestamp":1773482971352,"sessionID":"ses_3143289ffffebE5N0evuhJd5Hx","part":{"id":"prt_cebd28613001qQ4ZOtWMs1DEG2","sessionID":"ses_3143289ffffebE5N0evuhJd5Hx","messageID":"msg_cebd27ccb001QRmUNit2StMfy4","type":"text","text":"Good — the headless path already prints \"reconnected to PID\" when it actually reconnects. Now let me also check — the `toLaunchNow` calculation might cause an issue. If there are 0 items in `toLaunchNow` AND there are `stillAlive` agents, the current code bails out at line 382. But with `stillAlive` agents we should still enter the monitoring loop! Let me check:","time":{"start":1773482971352,"end":1773482971352}}}
