{"type":"text","timestamp":1773483004668,"sessionID":"ses_3143289ffffebE5N0evuhJd5Hx","part":{"id":"prt_cebd302b5001jKYN71zH3Fl7yQ","sessionID":"ses_3143289ffffebE5N0evuhJd5Hx","messageID":"msg_cebd2fa8a001av26jZksBPOdyZ","type":"text","text":"In `launch.ts`, the polling loop condition `!isProcessRunning(agent.pid) && !monitor.isRunning(agent.feature_id)` works correctly. When a reconnected agent's PID dies, `monitor.isRunning()` will return `false` (since `m.done` is set to `true` by the polling interval). But wait — there's a subtlety: the reconnected process's polling interval fires `onComplete` which triggers `handleBuildVerification` through the callback. Then the resume.ts polling loop ALSO checks `!isProcessRunning && !monitor.isRunning` — which would double-trigger.\n\nLet me check the condition more carefully in resume.ts:","time":{"start":1773483004668,"end":1773483004668}}}
