{"type":"text","timestamp":1773483010883,"sessionID":"ses_3143289ffffebE5N0evuhJd5Hx","part":{"id":"prt_cebd31bb7001R3lb5dTYFI4FmJ","sessionID":"ses_3143289ffffebE5N0evuhJd5Hx","messageID":"msg_cebd31380001we5LesS2iGLLbM","type":"text","text":"OK, I see the potential race condition. When the reconnected process's internal polling interval detects PID death:\n1. It fires `onComplete` → which changes agent status to `\"completed\"` \n2. The resume.ts polling loop condition checks `agent.status === \"running\"` — but since `onComplete` already changed it to `\"completed\"`, the condition is `false` and won't double-trigger\n\nSo there's no double-trigger issue. The `onComplete` callback handles the transition from \"running\" to \"completed\" → build verification. The polling loop in resume.ts only catches agents that somehow fell through without the callback.\n\nThis is correct. Let me now review the complete changes once more:","time":{"start":1773483010883,"end":1773483010883}}}
