{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":1773483033217,"sessionID":"ses_3143289ffffebE5N0evuhJd5Hx","part":{"id":"prt_cebd3652f001sOlKC0AlDQr2Jb","sessionID":"ses_3143289ffffebE5N0evuhJd5Hx","messageID":"msg_cebd35a230012jABMybj6wyB8D","type":"tool","callID":"toolu_vrtx_01ANGYhvTVbEjgq8vJSpYaF7","tool":"bash","state":{"status":"completed","input":{"command":"git add src/lib/monitor.ts src/commands/resume.ts && git commit -m \"feat(wave-reconnect): reconnect to running agents on resume\n\nWhen resuming a wave with 'woco resume', agents whose PIDs are still alive\n(typically interactive mux-based agents) are now reconnected to the\nProcessMonitor instead of being silently ignored.\n\nChanges:\n- Add reconnectProcess() to ProcessMonitor: creates a PID-only monitor\n  entry with no ChildProcess handle, loads historical log activity for\n  TUI context, and polls for PID death to trigger completion callbacks\n- Make MonitoredProcess.process nullable with explicit pid field to\n  support reconnected entries alongside normal ChildProcess-backed ones\n- Update isRunning() to use explicit pid field instead of process.pid\n- Update remove() to use process.kill(pid, signal) for reconnected\n  processes that have no ChildProcess handle\n- Update killAll() to skip killing reconnected processes (they are\n  independent agents that should survive the parent's exit)\n- Update resume.ts triage to track stillAlive agents and reconnect\n  them in the headless monitoring path\n- Fix early return in resume.ts that prevented entering the monitoring\n  loop when all agents were still alive (no re-launches needed)\"","description":"Commit wave-reconnect implementation"},"output":"[feature/wave-reconnect 78a6d45] feat(wave-reconnect): reconnect to running agents on resume\n 2 files changed, 141 insertions(+), 9 deletions(-)\n","title":"Commit wave-reconnect implementation","metadata":{"output":"[feature/wave-reconnect 78a6d45] feat(wave-reconnect): reconnect to running agents on resume\n 2 files changed, 141 insertions(+), 9 deletions(-)\n","exit":0,"description":"Commit wave-reconnect implementation","truncated":false},"time":{"start":1773483033100,"end":1773483033216}}}}
