{"type":"text","timestamp":1773483050824,"sessionID":"ses_3143289ffffebE5N0evuhJd5Hx","part":{"id":"prt_cebd39cdd002jSnhQt3hzlqGhh","sessionID":"ses_3143289ffffebE5N0evuhJd5Hx","messageID":"msg_cebd3915d001qUZoZB3gCRSv6d","type":"text","text":"All tasks are complete. Here's a summary of what was implemented:\n\n## Summary\n\n### Problem\nWhen a user quit the wave monitor TUI while agents were still running, then resumed with `woco resume`, the system would detect still-alive PIDs but just print \"leaving alone\" and skip them entirely. This meant:\n- No TUI activity display for those agents\n- No polling to detect when they finished\n- No automatic build verification when they completed\n- If no other agents needed re-launching, the resume would exit immediately\n\n### Solution\nTwo files were modified:\n\n**`src/lib/monitor.ts`** — ProcessMonitor changes:\n1. **`MonitoredProcess` interface**: Made `process` field nullable (`ChildProcess | null`), added explicit `pid` field and `reconnected` flag\n2. **`reconnectProcess()` method**: Creates a PID-only monitor entry, loads historical activity from log files for TUI context, starts a 2s polling interval to detect PID death and fire `onComplete` callbacks\n3. **`_loadHistoricalActivity()`**: Reads the last 50 lines from the agent's log file, parses JSON events for structured activity display in the TUI\n4. **`isRunning()`**: Now uses `m.pid` instead of `m.process.pid!` — works for both normal and reconnected processes\n5. **`remove()`**: For reconnected processes (no ChildProcess), uses `process.kill(pid, 'SIGTERM')` directly\n6. **`killAll()`**: Reconnected processes are NOT killed on shutdown — they're independent mux agents that should survive\n\n**`src/commands/resume.ts`** — Resume flow changes:\n1. Added `stillAlive` array to track agents whose PIDs are still running\n2. After creating the ProcessMonitor, calls `monitor.reconnectProcess()` for each alive agent\n3. Fixed early return condition: `toLaunchNow.length === 0 && stillAlive.length === 0` — ensures the monitoring loop starts even when the only work is reconnecting to existing agents\n4. Updated status messages to show reconnection count","time":{"start":1773483050823,"end":1773483050823}}}
